===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|addledd}}, {{m|enm|adyld}}, equivalent to {{af|en|addle|t1=[[urine]], [[liquid]] [[filth]]|-ed}}.  ''Addle'' derives from {{der|en|ang|adel}}, {{m|ang|adela|t=[[mud]], [[mire]], liquid [[manure]]}}, cognate with {{cog|gmq-osw|adel||urine}}, {{cog|gml|adel}}, Dutch {{m|nl|aal||[[manure]]}}. Used in [[noun phrase]] ''addle egg'' (mid-13c.) “egg that does not [[hatch]], [[rotten]] egg”, lit. “urine egg”, a [[loan translation]] of {{cog|la|ovum urinum}}, which is itself an [[erroneous]] loan translation of {{cog|grc|οὔριον ᾠόν||putrid egg}}, lit. “[[wind]] egg”, from {{m|grc|οὔριος||of the wind}}, from {{m|grc|οὖρος||fair wind}} (confused by Roman writers with {{m|grc|οὔριος||of urine}}, from {{m|grc|οὖρον||urine}}). Because of this usage, the noun in English was taken as an adj. from c. 1600, meaning “putrid”.

